<subSubSection id="C33502C489354B36D5CBFE48FB79FCA5" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B90514F89354B36D5CBFE48FB79FCA5" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D5CBFE48FEB1FE68" bold="true" box="[199,332,476,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D7EEFE48FB58FE68" authority="Marshall. The" authorityName="Marshall. The" box="[738,1189,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maerens">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D7EEFE48FC0CFE69" box="[738,1009,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Afrosmicronyx maerens</emphasis>
Marshall. The
</taxonomicName>
two species can be distinguished by the colour of the coating (black in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D7D7FD94FC93FD85" authorityName="Haran &amp; Perrin" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[731,878,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angolanus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D7D7FD94FC93FD85" box="[731,878,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89354B36D7D7FD94FD12FD8A" box="[731,751,512,535]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">A</collectingRegion>
. angolanus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, variegated grayish and brownish in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D002FD94FA71FD85" box="[1294,1420,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maerens">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D002FD94FA71FD85" box="[1294,1420,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89354B36D002FD94FADFFD8A" box="[1294,1314,512,535]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">A</collectingRegion>
. maerens
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the tooth on the protibiae (present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D734FDB0FD31FDA0" authorityName="Haran &amp; Perrin" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[568,716,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angolanus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D734FDB0FD31FDA0" box="[568,716,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89354B36D734FDB0FDB1FDA6" box="[568,588,548,571]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">A</collectingRegion>
. angolanus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tibiae only thickened in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D6E6FDB0FB95FDA1" box="[1002,1128,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maerens">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D6E6FDB0FB95FDA1" box="[1002,1128,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89354B36D6E6FDB0FC03FDA6" box="[1002,1022,548,571]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">A</collectingRegion>
. maerens
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the shape of the penis (sides rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D46CFDDCFE08FDFD" authorityName="Haran &amp; Perrin" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[352,501,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angolanus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D46CFDDCFE08FDFD" box="[352,501,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89354B36D46CFDDCFE88FDC2" box="[352,373,584,607]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">A</collectingRegion>
. angolanus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, narrowed in apical half in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D620FDDCFC57FDFD" box="[812,938,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maerens">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D620FDDCFC57FDFD" box="[812,938,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89354B36D620FDDCFCBDFDC2" box="[812,832,584,607]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">A</collectingRegion>
. maerens
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Hustache placed this species, with doubts, in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D45CFDF8FE07FD18" box="[336,506,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Chalybodontus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D45CFDF8FE07FD18" box="[336,506,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Chalybodontus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D72EFDF9FC98FD18" authority="(Hustache, 1935)" authorityName="Hustache" authorityYear="1935" baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[546,869,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Smicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D72EFDF9FD6AFD19" box="[546,663,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Smicronyx</emphasis>
(Hustache, 1935)
</taxonomicName>
. It is here transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D173FDF8FADCFD19" authorityName="Hustache" authorityYear="1935" box="[1151,1313,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D173FDF8FADCFD19" box="[1151,1313,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Afrosmicronyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the presence of scales on all of its elytra, the presence of a ventral tooth on the femora and tibiae as well as its Afrotropical distribution. Contrary to what is stated in the description, the rostrum bears a ventral tooth at its base. This condition is encountered in all species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D7D7FD4CFC83FD6D" authorityName="Hustache" authorityYear="1935" box="[731,894,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D7D7FD4CFC83FD6D" box="[731,894,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Afrosmicronyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore not restricted to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89354B36D59BFD68FEBCFC88" box="[151,321,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Chalybodontus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89354B36D59BFD68FEBCFC88" box="[151,321,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Chalybodontus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Of the several 
<typeStatus id="5494EFED89354B36D4F7FD69FDD6FC88" box="[507,555,765,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">type</typeStatus>
specimens mentioned by Hustache, the one used for description (with labels corresponding to the 
<typeStatus id="5494EFED89354B36D488FCB4FE49FCA5" box="[388,436,800,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">type</typeStatus>
locality) was located in the Hoffmann collection (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE2CBE89354B36D6EBFC8BFB8AFCA5" author="Perrin" box="[999,1143,799,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" refString="Perrin, H. (1998) Les types des especes afrotropicales du genre Curculio Linne, 1758 (Coleoptera, Curculionidae). Revue francaise d'Entomologie, 20 (4), 135 - 141." type="journal article" year="1998">Perrin, 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
